<p>I have an iPhone app that records lat and lng and posts it to a rails database, these points belong to a controller called drive. How can I save each lat and lng separately and belong to a drive that gets created.</p>  <pre><code>module Api   module V1     class DrivesController &lt; ApplicationController       skip_before_filter  :verify_authenticity_token       respond_to :json       def drive_params         params.require(:drive).permit(positions_attributes: [:latitude, :longitude, :signalStrength, :carrier, :zipcode, :city, :state, :signalType])       end       def create         @drive = Drive.create(drive_params)         @position = @drive.positions.build()         respond_to do |format|             if @drive.save               format.json { render json: "Saved"}             else               format.json { render json: "Did not Save", status: :unprocessable_entity }             end         end       end     end   end end </code></pre>  <p>Drive Model</p>  <pre><code>class Drive   include Mongoid::Document   has_many :positions end </code></pre>  <p>Position Model</p>  <pre><code>class Position   include Mongoid::Document   include Mongoid::Timestamps    belongs_to :drive    field :longitude, type: String   field :latitude, type: String end </code></pre>